<PubmedArticleSet>
<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="MEDLINE" Owner="NLM" IndexingMethod="Automated"><PMID Version="1">41812495</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2026</Year><Month>03</Month><Day>27</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2026</Year><Month>03</Month><Day>27</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print-Electronic"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1873-3557</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>355</Volume><PubDate><Year>2026</Year><Month>Jul</Month><Day>05</Day></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Spectrochimica acta. Part A, Molecular and biomolecular spectroscopy</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Spectrochim Acta A Mol Biomol Spectrosc</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>The water-soluble red CsPbI<sub>3</sub> perovskite quantum dot "on-off-on" fluorescence sensor for the detection of Cu<sup>2+</sup> and D-penicillamine.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>127698</StartPage><MedlinePgn>127698</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1016/j.saa.2026.127698</ELocationID><ELocationID EIdType="pii" ValidYN="Y">S1386-1425(26)00269-6</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>In this study, a water-soluble perovskite quantum dot (PQDs) based on CsPbI<sub>3</sub> "on-off-on" fluorescent probe was successfully constructed. The probe exhibits red fluorescence emission at 660&#xa0;nm under 465&#xa0;nm excitation, and the response mechanism of Cu<sup>2+</sup>-induced fluorescence quenching (OFF) and D-penicillamine (D-PA) triggered fluorescence recovery (ON) is realized. In addition, the dual target detection platform of both copper ions (Cu<sup>2+</sup>) and D-PA was established. Quantitative analysis showed that the detection linearity range was 0.5-15&#xa0;&#x3bc;M (LOD&#xa0;=&#xa0;0.21&#xa0;&#x3bc;M) for Cu<sup>2+</sup> and 0.4-60&#xa0;&#x3bc;M (LOD&#xa0;=&#xa0;16.7&#xa0;nM) for D-PA. Meanwhile, D-PA can be semi-quantitatively measured based on the change in solution color. The fluorescent probe provides a fast response time, high sensitivity, and convenient solution for real-time detection of Cu<sup>2+</sup> and D-PA. And it was applied in the determination of D-PA in serum samples with satisfactory results. It is particularly noteworthy that the synthesized perovskite quantum dots exhibit excellent stability in the aqueous environment, which provides a new strategy for expanding the application of perovskite materials in the field of biomedical analysis.</AbstractText><CopyrightInformation>Copyright &#xa9; 2026 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.</CopyrightInformation></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Pang</LastName><ForeName>Mengjiao</ForeName><Initials>M</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Pharmacy, Guangdong Pharmaceutical University, Guangzhou Higher Education Mega Center, Guangzhou 510006, PR China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Wang</LastName><ForeName>Yanjie</ForeName><Initials>Y</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Pharmacy, Guangdong Pharmaceutical University, Guangzhou Higher Education Mega Center, Guangzhou 510006, PR China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Du</LastName><ForeName>Zengcheng</ForeName><Initials>Z</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Pharmacy, Guangdong Pharmaceutical University, Guangzhou Higher Education Mega Center, Guangzhou 510006, PR China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Chen</LastName><ForeName>Qiqing</ForeName><Initials>Q</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Pharmacy, Guangdong Pharmaceutical University, Guangzhou Higher Education Mega Center, Guangzhou 510006, PR China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Liu</LastName><ForeName>Wenhao</ForeName><Initials>W</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Pharmacy, Guangdong Pharmaceutical University, Guangzhou Higher Education Mega Center, Guangzhou 510006, PR China.</Affiliation></Affi